ncy management and MBean registration**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the situation where the first run might fail after MBean registration due to a NoClassDef error related to Hibernate. In that case, MBean registration would happen, but without successful coverage. If I include the dependency, it helps with future runs, ensuring that the MBean can be located. Maybe I could wait for the MBean and then use `Thread.sleep(100)`. Another option is configuring a named session factory, using empty properties instead. I could consider creating a fake SessionFactory, but it seems I might need direct reflection for that. Let's figure this out!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating MBean configuration**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the JMX registration for the Standard MBean. It seems I might need to consider introspection reflection for it. The agent takes care of some aspects. I’ve already checked existing MBean tests, but I realize I need to add a dependency to build.gradle. There’s a chance that hibernate-core might bring in cglib and maybe even javassist dynamic for the native image, though I haven’t figured out how to use that yet.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_f9kLWhbDnklTro36InzsgRSK|fc_0acca6cc565cd4860169f55eccc208819da567ccbddc5728dd", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sf.ehcache/ehcache-core/2.4.4/src/test/java/net_sf_ehcache/ehcache_core/ProviderMBeanRegistrationHelperTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage net_sf_ehcache.ehcache_core;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.lang.management.ManagementFactory;\nimport java.util.Properties;\n\nimport javax.management.MBeanServer;\nimport javax.management.ObjectName;\n\nimport net.sf.ehcache.CacheManager;\nimport net.sf.ehcache.config.Configuration;\nimport net.sf.ehcache.hibernate.management.impl.ProviderMBeanRegistrationHelper;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ProviderMBeanRegistrationHelperTest {\n    private static final String CACHE_MANAGER_NAME = \"provider-mbean-registration-helper-coverage\";\n    private static final long REGISTRATION_TIMEOUT_MILLIS = 5_000L;\n    private static final long POLL_INTERVAL_MILLIS = 50L;\n\n    @Test\n    void registersHibernateMBeanAndScansUnnamedSessionFactories() throws Exception {\n        String previousTcActive = System.getProperty(\"tc.active\");\n        CacheManager cacheManager = newCacheManager();\n        ProviderMBeanRegistrationHelper helper = new ProviderMBeanRegistrationHelper();\n        ObjectName objectName = new ObjectName(\"net.sf.ehcache.hibernate:type=EhcacheHibernateStats,name=\" + CACHE_MANAGER_NAME);\n        MBeanServer mBeanServer = ManagementFactory.getPlatformMBeanServer();\n        try {\n            System.setProperty(\"tc.active\", \"true\");\n\n            helper.registerMBean(cacheManager, new Properties());\n\n            awaitMBeanRegistration(mBeanServer, objectName);\n            assertThat(mBeanServer.isRegistered(objectName)).isTrue();\n        } finally {\n            helper.unregisterMBean();\n            cacheManager.shutdown();\n            restoreTcActive(previousTcActive);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static CacheManager newCacheManager() {\n        Configuration configuration = new Configuration()\n                .name(CACHE_MANAGER_NAME)\n                .updateCheck(false);\n        return new CacheManager(configuration);\n    }\n\n    private static void awaitMBeanRegistration(MBeanServer mBeanServer, ObjectName objectName) throws InterruptedException {\n        long deadline = System.currentTimeMillis() + REGISTRATION_TIMEOUT_MILLIS;\n        while (!mBeanServer.isRegistered(objectName) && System.currentTimeMillis() < deadline) {\n            Thread.sleep(POLL_INTERVAL_MILLIS);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreTcActive(String previousTcActive) {\n        if (previousTcActive == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(\"tc.active\");\n            return;\n        }\n        System.setProperty(\"tc.active\", previousTcActive);\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1350, "output": 1883, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37025, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777688249736, "responseId": "resp_0acca6cc565cd4860169f55eba305c819da3c3f90080a50625"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_f9kLWhbDnklTro36InzsgRSK|fc_0acca6cc565cd4860169f55eccc208819da567ccbddc5728dd", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2730 bytes to tests/src/net.sf.ehcache/ehcache-core/2.4.4/src/test/java/net_sf_ehcache/ehcache_core/ProviderMBeanRegistrationHelperTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777688272405}]}
